<article id="node-6679">
<h1 >2.9 CCR Eligibility</h1>
<h2>Eligibility criteria for <a href="../family-assistance-guide/acronyms#ccr" title="Child care rebate">CCR</a></h2>
<p>An individual is eligible for the CCR for an income year if:</p>
<ul><li>the child care was provided by one or more approved child care services during at least one week in the year,</li>
<li>the individual was determined to be eligible for <a href="../family-assistance-guide/acronyms#ccb" title="Child care benefit">CCB</a> for the year (entitled at a rate of zero or more), and</li>
<li>the individual and partner (where applicable) met the CCR requirements of the work, training, study test for the week or, in the week, a weekly limit of hours applicable to the individual and the child was 50 hours, more than 50 hours or 24 hour care limit.</li>
</ul><p>An individual is eligible for fortnightly or quarterly payments of CCR if:</p>
<ul><li>the child care was provided by one or more approved child care services during at least one session or more during the week or at least one week in the quarter,</li>
<li>the individual was determined to be conditionally eligible for CCB by fee reduction,</li>
<li>CCB fee reductions were calculated for the individual and the child for that week (a more than nil amount or nil amount due to income), and</li>
<li>the individual and partner (where applicable) met the CCR requirements of the work, training, study test for the week or, in the week, a weekly limit of hours applicable to the individual and the child was 50 hours, more than 50 hours or 24 hour care limit.</li>
</ul><p>To satisfy the work, training, study test for the CCR an individual and partner (where applicable) only needs to have a work, or work related commitment at some point during the week (i.e. no minimum number of hours is required), or to have an exemption from this requirement.</p>
<p><strong>Note:</strong> An individual who is eligible for CCB in a week with a weekly limit of hours of 24 hours will also be eligible for receipt of CCR for the week, provided that the individual satisfies the work, training, study test at some time during the week, even if the number of hours is less than 15 in the week (or 30 over 2 weeks). This is because such an individual will be taken to have a weekly limit of hours of 50 hours for the purposes of eligibility for the CCR, under FAAct section 57EAA(1)(c), 57EA(1)(c), 57F(1)(c) or 57F(1A)(c), whichever applies.</p>
<div class="reference">
<p><strong>Act reference:</strong> <a href="https://www.legislation.gov.au/Series/C2004A00490" title="A New Tax System (Family Assistance) Act 1999">FAAct</a> section 42 When an individual is conditionally eligible for CCB by fee reduction for care provided by an approved child care service, section 43 When an individual is eligible for CCB by fee reduction for care provided by an approved child care service, section 44 When an individual is eligible for CCB for a past period for care provided by an approved child care service, section 57EAA Eligibility for CCR-for a week, section 57F Eligibility for CCR-for an income year or a period, section 57EA Eligibility for CCR-for a quarter</p>
<p><a href="https://www.legislation.gov.au/Series/C2004A00491" title="A New Tax System (Family Assistance) (Administration) Act 1999">FA(Admin)Act</a> section 65EAAAA Individual may elect to have CCR paid in various ways</p>
<p><strong>Policy reference:</strong> FA Guide <a href="../family-assistance-guide/1/1/e/17">1.1.E.17</a> Eligibility (FTB, SIFS, CCB &amp; CCR), <a href="../family-assistance-guide/1/2/7">1.2.7</a> Child Care Rebate (CCR) - Description, <a href="../family-assistance-guide/2/6/3/10">2.6.3.10</a> Eligibility Requirements for Up to 50 Hours CCB, <a href="../family-assistance-guide/2/6/3/20">2.6.3.20</a> Eligibility Requirements for More than 50 Hours CCB, <a href="../family-assistance-guide/1/1/i/90">1.1.I.90</a> Individual, <a href="../family-assistance-guide/1/1/p/30">1.1.P.30</a> Partner, partner in gaol</p>
</div>
